text: I'm not one to get too caught up in christian or feel good movies. However this trailer had me near tears when the doctors kept telling the mom there was nothing wrong or it wasn't a serious condition. As someone who has spent all of my teenage career having to fight with doctors who insist nothing is wrong with me, it struck a chord. You can't begin to imagine the frustration of being in pain on a hospital bed while a resident 'doctor' explains to your parents that you are making it up to avoid school. While I can't think of any scientific explanation for what happened to the little girl that healed her, this is one of those times where I'm willing to just accept the unexplainable and fall back on my faith. Because going through what she was going through is hell, and I'm glad that it's over for her. Sometimes it's okay to just accept a miracle.
